<TEXT>
<P>
 Judge Orders Bank, FDIC to Pay Landlord $115 Million: NationsBank Corp. and 
the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. have been ordered to pay $115 million to a 
Texas landlord after a judge ruled they bullied the landlord and improperly 
broke a lease. U.S. District Judge Joe Kendall wrote that the Charlotte, 
N.C.-based bank and the FDIC had operated in an "outrageous" manner with a 
"lack of regard for the rights of others" in trying to get rent breaks from 
Burnett Plaza Associates, the main owner of the building in question, a 
40-story office tower in Ft. Worth, Tex. 
