<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP PLAYOFFS AT A GLANCE; CITY SECTION BOYS' AND GIRLS' SWIMMING FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SHEPARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Today's schedule: Finals begin at 3 p.m. at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Last year's champions: Boys -- Van Nuys Birmingham; Girls -- Palisades. 
</P>
<P>
 * Outlook: Kristine Quance of Granada Hills dominated the City Section in 
swimming for several years, setting numerous records. Quance is at USC, but 
sophomore Gretchen Ballard of Van Nuys Birmingham hopes to take her place. 
Ballard has been unbeatable all year and has the fastest qualifying times in 
the 200 and 500 freestyle. Her 200 preliminary time of 1:54.07 last week was 
close to a meet record. She hopes her efforts can help Birmingham stop 
defending champion Palisades. The boys' competition is wide open. Junior 
Russell Perkins of Eagle Rock recorded impressive preliminary times in the 50 
and 100 freestyle of 21.80 and 48.55 seconds, respectively. ERIC SHEPARD 
</P>
