<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA HERO ENDS LAYOFF, WINS FEATURE AT BELMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sea Hero, last year's Kentucky Derby and Travers winner, ended an eight-month 
layoff by winning the $40,000 allowance feature at Belmont Park on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea Hero, ridden by Jerry Bailey and assigned high weight of 119 pounds, 
showed no signs of rustiness.The 4-year-old son of Polish Navy raced within 
easy striking distance of leader Dominant Prospect until the field turned for 
home, then pulled away to beat Rocking Josh by 1 1/4 lengths in 1:22 3/5 for 
the seven furlongs. 
</P>
<P>
 The race, originally to be run on turf, was moved to the muddy main track. It 
was Sea Hero's sixth victory in 17 career starts. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea Hero, the favorite, returned $5.40, $4.20 and $2.40. Rocking Josh paid 
$4.80 and $2.40 and Dominant Prospect returned $2.40. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm glad it's over," trainer Mack Miller said of the layoff. "I liked (the 
victory) very much because he's really not a sprinter, he's a router." 
</P>
