<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAROLA GOYA; CHOREOGRAPHER, EXPERT ON SPANISH DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carola Goya, 88, American expert on the Spanish dance who was believed to be 
the first solo castanets player. The daughter of New York actors manager Samuel 
Weller, she legally adopted the Spanish surname.Miss Goya was trained in ballet 
and studied Spanish dance in New York and Madrid. As dancer, choreographer and 
castanets virtuoso, she fused Spanish rhythms with classical music. She danced 
as a teen-ager with the New York Metropolitan Opera Ballet and later toured 
with the Jose Greco Dance Company. She appeared as a castanets soloist with the 
Detroit Symphony, the Kansas City Philharmonic, the Symphony of the Air and 
other groups. In 1954, Miss Goya performed and taught with Matteo Vittucci; 
they were married in 1974. She had directed the New York-based Foundation for 
Ethnic Dance since 1967. On Sunday in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
