(Tustin), Brian Butcher (Lakewood Mayfair), Jose Cabrerra (Estancia), Chris 
Clark (Kennedy), Mike Darr (Corona), Joe Garcia (La Quinta), David Glick 
(Palmdale), Jeff Hallock (La Mirada), Dan Harkey (Lakewood Mayfair), Brian 
Helsper (Tustin), Ed Hurtado (Corona), Ryan Kelley (Trabuco Hills), Jon 
Lauderdale (Tustin), C.J. Livernois (La Quinta), Jim Livernois (La Quinta), 
Charlie Marino (Kennedy), Gabe Miranda (Bishop Amat), Derek Nicholson (West 
Torrance), Freddy Ochoa (Mira Loma Jurupa Valley), Allen Paisano (Ridgecrest 
Burroughs), Pat Perez (La Mirada), Canaan Price (Palm Desert), Mike Rodriguez 
(Ontario Chaffey), Ryan Schmidt (Alta Loma), Chris Tapia (Lancaster Antelope 
Valley), Eric Valenzuela (Bishop Amat), Ryan Winmill (Tustin), Jim Yates (West 
Torrance), Tony Zuniga (Saddleback). 
</P>
<P>
 Best Draw: Corona. Not much standing in the way of the Panthers and a shot at 
third-seeded Palm Desert in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Worst Draw: Palm Desert. The Aztecs get a gimme in the first round, then will 
probably beat a solid La Mirada team and Corona to get to the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Notes: Bishop Amat, behind the pitching of Miranda (7-0, 0.17 ERA) and 
Valenzuela (10-0, 0.73 ERA), has been the class of this division since the 
season began. The Lancers opened with three consecutive shutouts and have 
closed even stronger, giving up only four runs in the last nine games. Seven of 
those were shutouts . . . La Quinta has also been streaking lately, but will 
need a big playoff from Livernois . . . Corona has the division's most 
dangerous duo in Darr (.513, 8 HR, 39 RBIs) and Hurtado (.419, 6 HR, 34 RBIs) . 
. . Take away the three Del Rey loses to Bishop Amat and St. John Bosco is 
18-3. The Braves also extended the Lancers in the season finale, losing, 9-3, 
in extra innings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
