<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Jenkins 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Crescenta Valley 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Swimming 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: After winning two races in the 1993 Southern Section 
Division II championships, Jenkins concentrated on swimming year-round for the 
first time. In March, he received his first invitation to the U.S. national 
championships. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: For the second year in a row, Jenkins won the 50- and 
100-yard freestyle races in the Division II finals Saturday night at Belmont 
Plaza in Long Beach. He also swam anchor legs on the victorious 200 and 400 
freestyle relays, leading the Falcons to a second-place team finish. Jenkins' 
split of 20.45 seconds in the 200 freestyle relay team helped the Falcons set a 
Division II record with a time of 1:26.75. "That record made the night 
worthwhile as a team. We didn't win the team title but we came away with 
something," Jenkins said. He was named the male swimmer of the meet for 
accumulating the most points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
