<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rebecca Gilman 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Buena 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Swimming 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Freshman 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Gilman was the final piece of the puzzle for Buena, which 
won the Division I title for the second time in three seasons. One of the best 
long-distance age-group freestylers in the nation, Gilman joined a veteran team 
that dominated the Channel League, one of the strongest swimming leagues in the 
Southern Section. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: In the Southern Section Division I finals Friday night, 
Gilman swam the anchor leg on the victorious 200-yard medley relay and won the 
200 freestyle to give the Bulldogs an overwhelming early lead. The Bulldogs 
finished with 221 points, 66 ahead of second-place Santa Barbara. Later in the 
evening, in the 500 freestyle, her automatic All-American time of 4:53.05 was 
more than four seconds faster than her closest pursuer. "It was a real exciting 
experience," Gilman said. "I felt great as soon as I hit the water." 
</P>
