<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; ACTRESS 
LYNN REDGRAVE FILES FOR BANKRUPTCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actress Lynn Regrave filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection in Los Angeles 
on Tuesday, her lawyer said.  
</P>
<P>
 In her filing, Redgrave, 51, contends that her financial problems began when 
MCA and Universal Television did not pay a 1987 court-ordered settlement to 
cover legal fees resulting from her 1981 wrongful dismissal lawsuit against the 
studio. 
</P>
<P>
 Efforts to recover the funds, as well as her pursuit of malpractice claims 
against her former lawyers, created additional expenses, according to her 
petition.  
</P>
<P>
 "These circumstances have left the actress in need of the court's protection 
while she reorganizes her financial affairs," said attorney David Neale of the 
Century City-based law firm of Levene & Eisenberg, which also is handling the 
bankruptcy cases of Zsa Zsa Gabor and Kim Basinger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
